v%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ring%20Nebula%20is%20a%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.westernu.ca%2F2023%2F08%2Fjwst-ring-nebula%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%C2%A0favorite%20among%20amateur%20astronomers%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Located%202%2C600%20light%20years%20from%20Earth%2C%20its%20bubble-like%20shape%20can%20be%20seen%20using%20a%20backyard%20telescope%20pointing%20at%20the%20Lyra%20constellation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20first%20saw%20the%20Ring%20Nebula%20as%20a%20kid%20through%20just%20a%20small%20telescope%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20astrophysicist%20Jan%20Cami%20of%20the%20University%20of%20Western%20Ontario%2C%20Canada%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20James%20Webb%20Space%20Telescope's%20(JWST)%20Ring%20Nebula%20Imaging%20Project%2C%20in%20a%20press%20release.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20never%20have%20thought%20that%20one%20day%2C%20I%20would%20be%20part%20of%20the%20team%20that%20would%20use%20the%20most%20powerful%20space%20telescope%20ever%20built%2C%20to%20look%20at%20this%20object%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20latest%20Ring%20Nebula%20picture%20isn't%20just%20%26quot%3Baesthetically%20pleasing%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20co-lead%20scientist%20Nick%20Cox%20of%20space%20observation%20firm%20ACRI-ST%2C%20France.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBy%20studying%20the%20Ring%20Nebula%20with%20JWST%2C%20we%20hope%20to%20gain%20a%20deeper%20understanding%20of%20the%20life%20cycles%20of%20stars%20and%20the%20elements%20they%20release%20into%20the%20cosmos%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20telescope's%20advanced%20infrared%20capabilities%20allow%20scientists%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjames-webb-space-telescope-has-captured-dazzling-images-of-cosmos-2022-8%5C%22%3Epeer%20through%20gas%20like%20never%20before%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20new%20picture%20is%20no%20exception%3B%20it%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%2