ore%20enforcement%20of%20heat-safety%20violations.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EBut%20this%20kind%20of%20legislation%20takes%20years%20to%20implement%2C%20and%20some%20states%20have%20even%20reversed%20similar%20laws.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EMillions%20of%20workers%20in%20the%20US%20have%20been%20struggling%20to%20do%20their%20jobs%20as%20the%20nation%20experiences%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftexas-heat-wave-weather-costs-economy-workers-jobs-2023-7%5C%22%3Efierce%20heat%20wave%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20new%20legislation%20may%20not%20be%20coming%20anytime%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20Biden%20administration%20has%20proposed%20federal%20protections%2C%20none%20have%20been%20finalized.%20This%20is%20partly%20due%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2Fjul%2F31%2Fheat-protections-workers-big-business-lobbies%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eopposition%20to%20similar%20proposals%20over%20the%20last%20few%20years%20from%20business%20lobbyists%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20construction%20and%20agriculture%20groups%20at%20the%20federal%20and%20state%20levels.%20Some%20argued%20in%20statements%20over%20the%20last%20two%20years%20that%20employers%20are%20already%20practicing%20fair%20labor%20standards%20and%20could%20be%20stretched%20thin%20if%20workers%20are%20allowed%20to%20take%20more%20time%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarc%20Freedman%2C%20vice%20president%20of%20employment%20policy%20at%20the%20United%20States%20Chamber%20of%20Commerce%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F31%2Fclimate%2Fheat-labor-productivity-climate.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etold%20The%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BI%20don't%20think%20anyone%20is%20dismissing%20the%20hazard%20of%20overexposure%20to%20heat%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20he%20asked%2C%20%26quot%3BIs%20an%20OSHA%20standard%20the%20right%20way%20to%20do%20it%3F%20A%20lot%20of%20employers%20are%20already%20taking%20measures%2C%20and%20the%20question%20will%20be%2C%20what%20more%20do%20they%20have%20to%20do%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlgernon%20Austin%2C%20director%20for%20race%20and%20economic%20justice%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Economic%20and%20Policy%20Research%2C%20told%20Insider%20his%20reading%20of%20the%20situation%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20companies%20are%20focused%20on%20short-term%2C%20quarterly%20profits.%26quot%3B%20He%20added%20that%20if%20companies%20%26quot%3Breduce%20the%20number%20of%20hours%20that%20workers%20are%20working%20because%20of%20extreme%20heat%2C%20then%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20lower%20output%2C%20and%20if%20they%20have%20lower%20output%2C%20then%20they're%20going%20to%20have%20lower%20sales%20and%20lower%20profits.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20shows%20%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheat-wave-puts-small-businesses-under-pressure-temperatures-bills-soar-2023-7%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22a24929c4b0773939b832951d360cc975%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%2220%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheat-wave-puts-small-businesses-under-pressure-temperatures-bills-soar-2023-7%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3Eheat-related%20productivity%20losses%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20holding%20the%20economy%20back%2C%20as%20employees%20are%20working%20fewer%20hours%20and%20working%20at%20slower%20rates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20week%2C%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2023%2F07%2F27%2Fremarks-by-president-biden-on-actions-to-protect-communities-from-extreme-heat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eannounced%20new%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protect%20workers%20from%20extreme%20heat%2C%20including%20directing%20the%20Labor%20Department%20to%20issue%20a%20Hazard%20Alert%20and%20better%20enforce%20heat-safety%20violations%20and%20inspections%20at%20agriculture%20and%20construction%20sites.%20As%20part%20of%20these%20plans%2C%20the%20National%20Oceanic%20and%20Atmospheric%20Administration%20committed%20to%20invest%20as%20much%20as%20%247%20million%20to%20improve%20the%20detail%20and%20accuracy%20of%20weather%20forecasts.%20In%20California%2C%20Colorado%2C%20and%20Washington%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20the%20Interior%20is%20investing%20%24152%20million%20on%20climate%20resilience%20and%20water%20storage%20efforts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMore%20than%2050%20Democratic%20and%20independent%20lawmakers%20introduced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brown.senate.gov%2Fimo%2Fmedia%2Fdoc%2Fasuncin_valdivia_heat_stress_injury_illness_and_fatality_prevention1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20bill%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20House%20and%20Senate%20last%20week%20that%20would%20push%20the%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%20to%20develop%20interim%20heat%20safety%20standards.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20number%201%20weather-related%20killer%20is%20heat.%20Six%20hundred%20people%20die%20annually%20from%20its%20effects%20%E2%80%94%20more%20than%20from%20floods%2C%20hurricanes%20and%20tornadoes%20in%20America%20combined%2C%26quot%3B%20Biden%20said%20last%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20OSHA%20has%20been%20working%20to%20create%20a%20national%20standard%20for%20workplace%20heat-safety%20rules%2C%20that%20process%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gao.gov%2Fproducts%2Fgao-12-330%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoften%20takes%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20and%20sometimes%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20to%20finalize.%20OSHA%2C%20which%20has%20recently%20increased%20its%20heat-related%20inspections%2C%20began%20developing%20heat%20standards%20in%202021%2C%20though%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nbcnews.com%2Fpolitics%2Fpolitics-news%2Fdemocrats-move-ramp-heat-safety-protections-workers-rcna96075%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20regulatory%20experts%20believe%3C%2Fa%3E%20OSHA%20is%20still%20over%20two%20years%20away%20from%20putting%20into%20place%20a%20final%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Democrats%20have%20considered%20these%20plans%20modest%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcasar.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fcasar.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2Fcongressional-letter-to-biden-administration-on-extreme-heat.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E112%20Democratic%20Congressmen%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20on%20the%20Biden%20administration%20to%20develop%20heat%20safety%20regulations%20for%20indoor%20and%20outdoor%20workplaces%2C%20which%20include%20protections%20such%20as%20water%2C%20rest%20breaks%2C%20and%20medical%20trainings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20heat%20waves%20are%20dangerous%2C%20they%20are%20life-threatening%2C%20and%20%E2%80%93%20with%20the%20devastating%20effects%20of%20climate%20change%20%E2%80%93%20they%20are%20only%20getting%20worse%2C%26quot%3B%20Senator%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20who%20signed%20the%20letter%2C%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%20%26quot%3BI%20urge%20the%20administration%20to%20move%20quickly%20to%20create%20this%20national%20heat%20standard%20to%20protect%20workers%20on%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20with%20no%20federal%20regulations%20that%20protect%20workers%20in%20hot%20conditions%2C%20many%20workers%20are%20left%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20continue%20subjecting%20themselves%20to%20extreme%20heat%20to%20make%20ends%20meet%20or%20reduce%20their%20hours%20to%20stay%20safe.%20Some%20companies%20have%20already%20provided%20more%20resources%20to%20employees%20such%20as%20cold%20water%20or%20new%20uniforms%2C%20though%20without%20nationwide%20regulations%20for%20water%20breaks%20or%20reduced%20hours%2C%20some%20workers%20have%20no%20choice%20but%20to%20brave%20the%20high%20temperatures.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EStates%20haven't%20made%20much%20progress%20on%20protecting%20workers%2C%20and%20some%20have%20even%20rolled%20back%20heat%20safety%20standards%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOnly%20a%20handful%20of%20states%20have%20passed%20heat-related%20labor%20protections%2C%20a%20perhaps%20surprising%20statistic%20given%20that%20in%202020%2C%20heat%20exposure%20cost%20the%20US%20economy%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fonebillionresilient.org%2Fextreme-heat-the-economic-and-social-consequences-for-the-united-states%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DAmong%2520the%2520report%2527s%2520key%2520findings%2Cafflicting%2520Black%2520and%2520Hispanic%2520workers.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earound%20%24100%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20loss%20of%20productivity.%20This%20value%20is%20expected%20to%20grow%20to%20%24500%20billion%20by%202050.%20Last%20year%2C%20business%20groups%20sued%20Oregon%20over%20extreme%20heat%20worker%20protection%20rules%2C%20arguing%20the%20state%20overstepped%20its%20statutory%20authority%20in%20requiring%20employers%20to%20pay%20workers%20during%20breaks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETexas%2C%20which%20has%20recently%20rolled%20back%20some%20legislation%20mandating%20water%20breaks%2C%20contributes%20to%20nearly%20a%20third%20of%20the%20nation's%20labor%20productivity%20losses%2C%20or%20around%20%2430%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20states%20including%20California%2C%20Michigan%2C%20and%20Georgia%2C%20Amazon%20workers%20have%20gone%20on%20strike%20over%20the%20company's%20labor%20practices%2C%20partly%20in%20response%20to%20complaints%20about%20heat%20exposure%20and%20lack%20of%20air%20conditioning%20in%20delivery%20vans.%20Around%20340%2C000%20UPS%20workers%20went%20on%20strike%20in%20part%20because%20of%20extreme%20heat%20%E2%80%94%20between%202015%20and%202022%2C%20at%20least%20143%20UPS%20employees%20were%20hospitalized%20for%20heat-related%20issues%2C%20according%20to%20the%20company's%20Occupational%20Safety%20and%20Health%20Administration%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20data-link-name%3D%5C%22in%20body%20link%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dropbox.com%2Fscl%2Ffi%2Fzn8e5v5w2odjaeltp8h10%2FJanuary2015toSeptember2022-OSHA-UPS.xls%3Fdl%3D0%26rlkey%3Drogyyt1ituhtimggo5j63utvc%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecords%3C%2Fa%3E.%20UPS%20agreed%20to%20install%20air%20conditioning%20in%20most%20delivery%20vehicles%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20all%20comes%20after%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.politico.com%2Fnews%2F2021%2F09%2F20%2Fbiden-workplace-safety-rule-heat-512966%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eyears%20of%20proposals%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20workplace%20safety%20rules%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bnational%20emphasis%20program%26quot%3B%20for%20heat%20inspections%20and%20%26quot%3Bunprogrammed%20inspections%26quot%3B%20by%20OSHA.%20The%20Asuncion%20Valdivia%20Heat%20Illness%20and%20Fatalities%20Prevention%20Act%20of%202022%20called%20for%20%26quot%3Ba%20standard%20that%20requires%20employers%20to%20implement%20certain%20measures%20for%20protecting%20workers%20from%20heat%20stress%20and%20related%20illnesses%20or%20injuries%2C%26quot%3B%20though%20Congress%20never%20took%20it%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20OSHA%20announcement%20in%202021%2C%20some%20powerful%20lobbyist%20groups%20spoke%20out%20against%20the%20proposed%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20OSHA%20moves%20forward%20with%20this%20process%2C%20it%20is%20imperative%20that%20OSHA%20avoids%20placing%20duplicative%20or%20overly%20burdensome%20regulations%20on%20our%20nation's%20producers%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdownloads.regulations.gov%2FOSHA-2021-0009-0770%2Fattachment_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20the%20American%20Farm%20Bureau%20Federation%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20comments%20after%20the%20announcement.%20The%20AFBF%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bvariances%20in%20agricultural%20work%20and%20climate%26quot%3B%20could%20make%20it%20difficult%20for%20OSHA%20to%20create%20solutions%20without%20imposing%20%26quot%3Bonerous%20burdens%20on%20farmers%20and%20ranchers%20that%20will%20lead%20to%20economic%20losses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.demolitionassociation.com%2FPortals%2F0%2FNDA%2520Submits%2520Comments%2520to%2520Congress%2520on%2520Heat%2520Exposure%2520Legislation%25281%2529_1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENational%20Demolition%20Association%20responded%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bissues%20of%20heat%20exposure%20and%20the%20means%20to%20address%20it%20on%20the%20variety%20of%20construction%20worksites%20across%20the%20country%20are%20extremely%20complex%2C%26quot%3B%20adding%20that%20defining%20what%20%26quot%3Bexcessive%20heat%26quot%3B%20means%20%26quot%3Bdepends%20upon%20personal%20characteristics.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F20%2Fclimate%2Fhow-extreme-heat-affects-workers-and-the-economy.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20experts%20believe%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20investments%20to%20protect%20workers%2C%20such%20as%20rearranging%20shifts%20or%20changing%20uniform%20colors%2C%20pay%20off%20since%20workers%20can%20be%20more%20productive%20in%20the%20longer%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20business%20community%20really%20needs%20to%20recognize%20that%20this%20is%20a%20real%20problem%20that%20you%20can't%20hide%20behind%2C%20that%20you%20absolutely%20have%20to%20address%2C%26quot%3B%20Austin%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou%20might%20as%20well%20start%20addressing%20it%20now%20rather%20than%20putting%20it%20off%20until%20you're%20forced%20to.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fheat-wave-safety-standards-at-work-biden-business-regulations%5C%22%3EBusiness%2