appointed%20amid%20a%20depressed%20housing%20market%20and%20high%20youth%20unemployment.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJust%2052%2C000%20tourists%20on%20trips%20organized%20by%20travel%20agents%20visited%20China%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%2C%20per%20the%20WSJ.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20struggling%20tourism%20sector%20will%20not%20help%20China's%20economy%20shake%20off%20its%20slowdown.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20world's%20second-largest%20economy%20is%20spluttering.%20China's%20been%20facing%20a%20slew%20of%20headwinds%20this%20year%2C%20such%20as%20a%20depressed%20housing%20market%2C%20rocketing%20youth%20unemployment%2C%20and%20widespread%20deflation%20fears.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGrowth%20for%20the%20second%20quarter%20came%20in%20at%206.3%25%2C%20falling%20short%20of%20analysts'%20forecasts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20also%20has%20another%20problem.%20Despite%20reopening%20to%20the%20world%20after%20the%20pandemic%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20it%20seems%20foreign%20visitors%20are%20not%20yet%20returning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%2052%2C000%20people%20arrived%20on%20visits%20organized%20by%20travel%20agents%20in%20the%20first%20quarter%20of%20the%20year%2C%20the%20most%20recent%20period%20for%20which%20figures%20are%20available%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fchinas-latest-problem-people-dont-want-to-go-there-7d17a83a%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20That's%2098%25%20lower%20than%20the%20same%20period%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20World%20Tourism%20Alliance%2C%20a%20Chinese%20tourism%20research%20outfit%2C%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wta-web.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F2023H1ChinaInboundTourismMarketSentimentReport03291_011.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20country's%20tourism%20sector%20was%20in%20a%20state%20of%20%26quot%3Bdistress%20and%20depression%26quot%3B%20following%20China's%20slow%20reopening%20after%20the%20pandemic.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20almost%20three%20years%2C%20the%20country%20was%20all%20but%20closed%20to%20business%20travelers%2C%20tourists%2C%20and%20even%20residents'%20families%20as%20part%20of%20the%20stringent%20%26quot%3Bzero-Covid%26quot%3B%20policy%20that%20was%20not%20abandoned%20until%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20possible%20that%20deteriorating%20relations%20with%20the%20West%20could%20be%20a%20factor%2C%20per%20the%20Journal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20late%20June%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftravel.state.gov%2Fcontent%2Ftravel%2Fen%2Finternational-travel%2FInternational-Travel-Country-Information-Pages%2FChina.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EState%20Department%20warned%20Americans%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20%26quot%3Breconsider%20travel%20to%20Mainland%20China%20due%20to%20the%20arbitrary%20enforcement%20of%20local%20laws%2C%20including%20in%20relation%20to%20exit%20bans%2C%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20wrongful%20detentions.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20visitors%20from%20Europe%2C%20America%2C%20Japan%20and%20Korea%20are%20all%20dropping%2C%20substantially%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Xiao%20Qianhui%2C%20a%20director%20of%20the%20China%20Tourism%20Association%2C%20in%20May.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20is%20far%20less%20dependent%20on%20tourism%20than%20other%20nations%20in%20the%20region%20industry%20such%20as%20Thailand%20and%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20has%20seen%20a%2090%25%20rebound%20in%20its%20tourism%20outflows%20to%20other%20countries%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lack%20of%20international%20appetite%20for%20visiting%20China%20will%20not%20do%20anything%20to%20boost%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20so%20far%20has%20stopped%20short%20of%20making%20any%20interventions%20despite%20pressure%20to%20stimulate%20a%20recovery%20in%20manufacturing%20and%20ser