inability%20space%20then.%20We%20were%20so%20happy%20when%20a%20retailer%20invested%20in%20us%2C%20which%20is%20rare%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rahul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECustomer%20reviews%20also%20buoyed%20the%20team.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20all%20in.%20I%20had%20sold%20my%20house%2C%20Arvind%20had%20sold%20his%20shares%2C%20and%20we%20exhausted%20our%20savings.%20When%20we%20saw%20a%20repeat%20purchase%20rate%20of%20more%20than%2030%20percent%2C%20we%20were%20ecstatic.%20It%20was%20the%20silver%20lining%20for%20us.%20Reading%20positive%20reviews%20about%20the%20quality%20felt%20great%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20founders%E2%80%99%2015%2B%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20big%20banks%20and%20corporates%2C%20combined%20with%20their%20bootstrapped%20approach%2C%20provided%20them%20with%20valuable%20discipline%20and%20perspective.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBeing%2040-year-olds%2C%20we%20have%20helped%20scale%20many%20companies%20and%20products.%20We%20used%20this%20experience%20and%20maturity%20when%20we%20started%20our%20business.%20It%20was%20a%20calculated%20risk.%20Not%20getting%20investment%2C%20in%20the%20beginning%2C%20was%20actually%20a%20blessing%20for%20us.%20We%20built%20a%20business%20model%20that%20was%20inherently%20profitable%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Rahul.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20advises%20budding%20entrepreneurs%20not%20to%20be%20swayed%20by%20the%20allure%20of%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEveryone%20thinks%20that%20starting%20your%20own%20company%20is%20glamorous.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not.%20There%20is%20nothing%20wrong%20with%20having%20a%20regular%20nine-to-five%20job.%20And%20even%20when%20you%20decide%20to%20start%20out%2C%20don%E2%80%99t%20build%20a%20company%20that%20survives%20on%20VC%20money.%20That%20is%20a%20dangerous%20business%20model%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Priyanka%20Aeron%2C%20India%20Managing%20Director%20and%20Head%20of%20Global%20HR%20%26amp%3B%20Tech%2C%