%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epropagated%20amongst%20the%20masses%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Anecdotes%20suggest%20during%20his%20later%20interactions%20with%20Gandhi%2C%20Munis%20even%20went%20on%20to%20teach%20the%20legend%20the%20language%2C%20a%20skill%20that%20greatly%20helped%20the%20latter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20persistent%20and%20vocal%20was%20he%20about%20his%20patriotic%20opinions%20that%20he%20was%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9Cnotorious%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cbitter%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdangerous%E2%80%9D%20by%20the%20British%2C%20eventually%20being%20branded%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Ebadmash%20patrakar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(rouge%20journalist)%3Cem%3E%E2%80%99%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20British%20Police%20document%20from%20the%20Azadi%20Ke%20Deewane%20Museum%20at%20Red%20Fort%20reads%2C%20%E2%80%9CPir%20Muhammed%20Munis%20is%20actually%20a%20dangerous%20and%20hoodlum%20journalist%20who%20through%20his%20questionable%20literature%2C%20brought%20to%20light%20the%20sufferings%20of%20a%20backward%20place%20like%20Champaran%20in%20Bihar.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20letter%20that%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20the%20uprising%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20480px)%20100vw%2C%20480px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDKZBgUiUEAA3QgY-1690548557.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pir%20Muhammed%20Munis%20fought%20for%20the%20farmers%20in%20the%20Champaran%20region%20of%20Bihar%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDKZBgUiUEAA3QgY-1690548557.jpg%20480w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDKZBgUiUEAA3QgY-1690548557-300x225.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2FDKZBgUiUEAA3QgY-1690548557-150x113.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-325633%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22360%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPir%20Muhammed%20Munis%20fought%20for%20the%20farmers%20in%20the%20Champaran%20region%20of%20Bihar%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Twitter%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FWeIndianMuslims%2Fstatus%2F1266577590824861699%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMuslims%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20nothing%20stopped%20Munis%20from%20continuing%20to%20write%2C%20his%20pen%20a%20double-edged%20sword.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F286447%2Fa-hero-to-bhagat-singh-this-punjabi-sacrificed-his-life-for-indias-freedom-at-19%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHis%20works%3C%2Fa%3E%20appeared%20frequently%20in%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20Hindi%20weekly%2C%20and%20monthlys%20such%20as%20%3Cem%3EGyanshakti%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20%3Cem%3EGorakhpur%3C%2Fem%3E.%20He%20was%20also%20on%20the%20editorial%20board%20of%20%3Cem%3EDesh%20%3C%2Fem%3Elaunched%20and%20edited%20by%20Dr%20Rajendra%20Prasad.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20famous%20letter%20among%20his%20repertoire%20of%20literary%20works%20is%20a%20letter%20he%20penned%20with%20local%20farmer%20Rajkumar%20Shukla%2C%20intended%20to%20be%20sent%20to%20Gandhi%20on%2027%20February%201917.%20Shukla%20conveyed%20the%20grievances%20of%20the%20farming%20community%2C%20while%20Munis%20coupled%20this%20with%20his%20power%20of%20words.%20An%20excerpt%20from%20the%20letter%20reads%2C%20%E2%80%9COur%20sad%20tale%20is%20much%20worse%20than%20what%20you%20and%20your%20comrades%20have%20suffered%20in%20South%20Africa%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20another%20letter%20dated%2022%20March%201917%2C%20Munis%20once%20again%20voiced%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F280138%2Fshaheed-bhagat-singh-death-anniversary-last-photograph-history-martyrs-day%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehis%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20peasants%20in%20Champaran%2C%20and%20asked%20Gandhi%20to%20pay%20them%20a%20visit.%20And%20when%20he%20did%20on%2010%20April%201917%2C%20people%20commended%20the%20bond%20between%20the%20two%2C%20often%20calling%20Munis%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20pillar%20as%20he%20hatched%20plans%20for%20the%20Champaran%20Satyagraha.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20first%20Satyagraha%20movement%2C%20it%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20future%20mass%20protests%20and%20uprisings.%20Gandhi%20set%20up%20schools%20in%20the%20Champaran%20area%2C%20gathered%20volunteers%2C%20conducted%20village%20surveys%2C%20organised%20protests%2C%20and%20strikes%2C%20and%20advocated%20for%20control%20over%20the%20sale%20of%20crops%20to%20be%20given%20to%20the%20farmers.%20And%20through%20this%20mutiny%2C%20Munis%20was%20by%20his%20side.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20did%20not%20go%20down%20well%20with%20the%20British.%20As%20a%20letter%20written%20by%20W%20H%20Lewis%2C%20sub-division%20officer%20to%20the%20commissioner%20of%20Tirhut%20division%20indicates%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20Mr%20Gandhi%20got%20offers%20of%20assistance%2C%20the%20most%20prominent%20is%20Pir%20Muhammad.%20I%20have%20not%20(sic)%20full%20details%20of%20his%20career%2C%20but%20either%20Whitty%20or%20Marsham%20could%20give%20them.%20He%20is%2C%20I%20believe%2C%20a%20convert%20to%20Muhammadanism%20and%20was%20a%20teacher%20in%20the%20Raj%20School.%20He%20was%20dismissed%20from%20his%20post%20for%20virulent%20attacks%20on%20local%20management%20published%20in%20or%20about%201915%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F267482%2Frrr-komaram-bheem-junior-ntr-gond-adivasi-nizam-hyderabad-telugu%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ein%20the%20press%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20lives%20in%20Bettiah%20and%20works%20as%20a%20press%20correspondent%20for%20the%20Pratap%20of%20Lucknow%2C%20a%20paper%20which%20distinguished%20itself%20for%20its%20immoderate%20expressions%20on%20Champaran%20Questions%E2%80%A6%20Pir%20Muhammad%20is%20the%20link%20between%20this%20Bettiah%20class%20of%20mostly%20educated%20and%20semi-educated%20men%20and%20the%20next%20class%2C%20i.e.%20the%20Raiyats%E2%80%99%20own%20leaders%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20result%20of%20the%20tyranny%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistory%20never%20forgets%20the%20cries%20of%20the%20just%2C%20and%20the%20Champaran%20Satyagraha%20was%20proof%20of%20this.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mutiny%20ended%20with%20the%20British%20officers%20agreeing%20to%20formulate%20the%20Champaran%20Agrarian%20Act%20of%201918.%20The%20Act%20abolished%20the%20forcible%20cultivation%20of%20indigo%20and%20thus%20relieved%20tremendous%20pressure%20being%20put%20on%20the%20farmers%20here.%20The%20event%20has%20gone%20down%20in%20history%20as%20one%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F264216%2Fsaifuddin-kitchlew-freedom-fighter-jallianwala-bagh-hindu-muslim-unity%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efirst%20major%20revolts%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20forced%20the%20English%20to%20introduce%20a%20Bill%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20Indians.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20Tinkathia%20system%20being%20abolished%2C%20the%20farmers%20thought%20the%20worst%20was%20over.%20But%20the%20British%20continued%20to%20oppress%20them%20in%20different%20ways.%20Fuelled%20by%20ending%20this%20once%20and%20for%20all%2C%20Munis%20started%20%3Cem%3ERaiyati%20Sabha%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20platform%20that%20would%20advocate%20for%20and%20protect%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20farming%20community.%20For%20this%2C%20Munis%20faced%20a%20six-month%20jail%20term.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20last%20of%20imprisonment.%20In%201930%20he%20was%20imprisoned%20in%20the%20Patna%20Camp%20jail%20for%20three%20months%20for%20his%20participation%20in%20the%20Salt%20Satyagraha%20of%20the%20Civil%20Disobedience%20Movement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20nothing%20could%20deter%20him%20from%20his%20goal%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F250530%2Fwoman-freedom-fighter-rani-gaidinliu-northeast-manipur-british-india-independence-inspiring-yos191%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprotecting%20the%20rights%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20his%20countrymen.%20In%201937%2C%20he%20led%20sugarcane%20producers%20who%20were%20protesting%20against%20intermediaries%20who%20were%20pocketing%20a%20major%20part%20of%20the%20earnings.%20He%20was%20also%20elected%20member%20of%20the%20Champaran%20Zila%20Parishad%20(District%20Board)%20on%20the%20Congress%20ticket%20and%20became%20President%20of%20Bettiah%20Local%20Board%2C%20from%20which%20he%20resigned%20to%20join%20the%20Individual%20Civil%20Disobedience%20Movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThroughout%20his%20lifetime%2C%20he%20advocated%20for%20rural%20development%2C%20popularisation%20of%20Hindi%20in%20primary%20schools%20and%20the%20rights%20of%20his%20fellow%20Indians.%20Until%20his%20passing%20away%20on%2023%20September%201949%20Munis%20continued%20to%20be%20a%20leader%20worth%20looking%20up%20to%20for%20his%20countrymen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELauding%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F229887%2Fmumbai-rama-khandwala-freedom-fighter-subhas-chandra-bose-national-award-best-tour-guide-india-gop94%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Munis%20on%20his%20passing%20away%2C%20%3Cem%3EPratap%3C%2Fem%3E%20editor%20Ganesh%20Shankar%20Vidyarthi%2C%20wrote%20in%20his%20newspaper%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20the%20utmost%20sorrow%20that%20Pir%20Muhammed%20Munis%20of%20Bettiah%2C%20Champaran%20district%20has%20died.%20We%20have%20the%20privilege%20to%20see%20such%20souls%20who%20are%20quietly%20lying%20aside.%20The%20world%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20come%20to%20know%20anything%20about%20their%20issues.%20The%20lesser%20these%20sons%20of%20Mother%20India%20are%20renowned%2C%20the%20more%20profound%20is%20their%20work%2C%20the%20more%20philanthropic.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20further%20wrote%2C%20%E2%80%9CYou%20recited%20the%20dreadful%20story%20of%20Champaran%20to%20Gandhi%20%3Cem%3Eji%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20this%20was%20a%20result%20of%20your%20hard-work%20only%20that%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20visited%20Champaran%20which%20made%20this%20land%20a%20pious%20place%20and%20the%20place%20which%20is%20unerasable%20in%20the%20pages%20of%20history%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ESources%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Findia%2Fon-hindi-diwas-here-s-the-story-of-pir-muhammad-munis-a-hindi-journalist-and-unsung-hero-of-champaran-satyagrah-329625.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20The%20Story%20Of%20Pir%20Muhammad%20Munis%2C%20A%20Hindi%20Journalist%20And%20Unsung%20Hero%20Of%20Champaran%20Satyagraha%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Afroz%20Alam%20Sahil%2C%20Published%20on%2010%20April%202018.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fh5%3E%5Cn%3Ch5%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.freepressjournal.in%2Findia%2Frepublic-day-2022-from-the-man-who-designed-the-tricolour-to-unsung-hero-of-pasighat-saluting-the-heroes-who-made-india-great%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERepublic%20Day%202022%3A%20From%20The%20man%20who%20designed%20the%20Tricolour%20to%20Unsung%20hero%20of%20Pasighat%E2%80%A6%20saluting%20the%20heroes%20who%20made%20India%20great%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Free%20Press%20Journal%2C%20Published%20on